      • stream

        public Stream<RDF4JTriple> stream()
        Description copied from interface: Graph
        Get all triples contained by the graph.

        The iteration does not contain any duplicate triples, as determined by the Triple.equals(Object) method for each Triple.

        The behaviour of the Stream is not specified if Graph.add(Triple), Graph.remove(Triple) or Graph.clear() are called on the Graph before it terminates.

        Implementations may throw ConcurrentModificationException from Stream methods if they detect a conflict while the Stream is active.

        Specified by:

      • getContextFilter

        public Optional<Resource[]> getContextFilter()
        Description copied from interface: RDF4JGraph
        Return a copy of the context filter, if present.

        If Optional.isPresent(), the filter determines which contexts in the corresponding RDF4J Model or Repository that this graph reflect. Modifications to the graph (e.g. Graph.add(Triple) will be performed for all the specified contexts, while retrieval (e.g. Graph.contains(Triple)) will succeed if the triple is in at least one of the specified contexts.

        The context filter array may contain null, indicating the default context (the default graph in RDF datasets).

        If the context filter is Optional.empty(), then this is a union graph which triples reflecting statements in any contexts. Triples added to the graph will be added in the default context null.

        The filter array is a copy, and thus any modifications are not reflected in the RDF4JGraph.

        Specified by:
        getContextFilter in interface RDF4JGraph
        Returns:
        The context filter as an array of Resources, or Optional.empty() indicating the union graph (any context).
